 <table-wrap-foot>
  <fn fn-type="other" id="T1F1">
   <label>a</label>
   <p>Samples are taken from 16 calves (8 inoculated and 8 contact infected). Most inoculated calves were euthanized before the early recovery phase, hence the lower number of samples tested in this phase.</p>
  </fn>
  <fn fn-type="other" id="T1F2">
   <label>b</label>
   <p>Cyclone samplers used for room sampling were a glass cyclone sampler and the Coriolis sampler. Because all samples were positive (sensitivity for each phase of infection of 100%), the lower 95% confidence limits were estimated by using the Wilson score method. This method is suitable for small sample sizes (
    <xref rid="B26" ref-type="bibr">26</xref>).
   </p>
  </fn>
